SIMPLE: point-blank
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Point-blank
<hw>Point`-blank"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>point</ets> point + <ets>blanc</ets> white.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The white spot on a target, at which an arrow or other missile is
aimed.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>With all small arms,
the second point in which the natural line of sight, when horizontal,
cuts the trajectory.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>With artillery, the point
where the projectile first strikes the horizontal plane on which the gun
stands, the axis of the piece being horizontal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Point-blank</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Point-blank
<hw>Point`-blank"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Directed in a
line toward the object aimed at; aimed directly toward the
mark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, direct; plain; unqualified; -- said of
language; <as>as, a <ex>point-blank</ex> assertion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Point-blank range</b></col>, <cd>the extent of the
apparent right line of a ball discharged.</cd> -- <col><b>Point-blank
shot</b></col>, <cd>the shot of a gun pointed directly toward the object
to be hit.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Point-blank</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Point-blank
<hw>Point`-blank"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a point-blank
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To sin <qex>point-blank</qex> against God's word.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Point d'appui</ent>⟦br⟧
<-- the following foreign words had no mark \'d8 in front, in the original. Why? -->
